1.4 "Commercial Use" includes, but is not limited to:

(a) use by or for a for-profit entity, including internal use;

(b) use in connection with providing, supporting, or developing goods
or services for which any consideration is received, directly or indirectly;

(c) use to develop, operate, or provide a hosted or managed service
(including SaaS) to third parties;

(d) distribution, sublicensing, licensing, selling, or monetizing the
Software or any derivative work;

(e) use where the Software is a dependency of software used for any of
the purposes described above;

(f) use by a contractor, consultant, or agent performing work for or on
behalf of a for-profit entity.

1.5 "Derivative Work" means any work based upon the Software, including
modifications, adaptations, translations, or works incorporating all or
part of the Software.

1.6 "Competing Product" means any product or service, whether commercial
or non-commercial, that provides functionality substantially similar to,
